nmsMEAPSRowStatus.name: nmsMEAPSRowStatus
nmsMEAPSRowStatus.description: A read-create value that indicates the configuration status of the domain instance. Set this value to 'enabled' to start the ring or 'disabled' to stop it. The value 'running' indicates that the domain is currently configured and running, in which case, the values of node-type and control-vlan cannot be modified.

nmsMEAPSRingControlVlanMajor.name: nmsMEAPSRingControlVlanMajor

nmsMEAPSRingState.name: nmsMEAPSRingState
nmsMEAPSRingState.description: A value indicates the state of a node in the ring. Only the value from a MasterNode indicates the state of the whole ring. The value from a TransitNode means the local ring ports are all operational or not.

nmsMEAPSRingHealthCheck.name: nmsMEAPSRingHealthCheck
nmsMEAPSRingHealthCheck.description: A value indicates whether Health packets are being sent from MasterNode. Available only for MasterNodes.

nmsMEAPSRingHelloTime.name: nmsMEAPSRingHelloTime
nmsMEAPSRingHelloTime.description: The inteval between the transmit of two Health packets, in seconds. Available only for MasterNodes.

nmsMEAPSRingFailTime.name: nmsMEAPSRingFailTime
nmsMEAPSRingFailTime.description: The hold time for the SecondaryPort after a Health packet is received, in seconds. Available only for MasterNodes.

nmsMEAPSRingPreforwardTime.name: nmsMEAPSRingPreforwardTime
nmsMEAPSRingPreforwardTime.description: The hold time for a TransitPort which is recovered from a failure, in seconds. During the pre-forward time, no packets other than PDUs in control vlan can be forwarded. Only available for TransitNodes.

nmsMEAPSRingEdgeHelloTime.name: nmsMEAPSRingEdgeHelloTime
nmsMEAPSRingEdgeHelloTime.description: The hold time for a TransitPort which is recovered from a failure, in seconds. During the pre-forward time, no packets other than PDUs in control vlan can be forwarded. Only available for TransitNodes.

nmsMEAPSRingEdgeFailTime.name: nmsMEAPSRingEdgeFailTime
nmsMEAPSRingEdgeFailTime.description: The hold time for a TransitPort which is recovered from a failure, in seconds. During the pre-forward time, no packets other than PDUs in control vlan can be forwarded. Only available for TransitNodes.

nmsMEAPSRingAdminStatus.name: nmsMEAPSRingAdminStatus
nmsMEAPSRingAdminStatus.description: A read-create value that indicates the configuration status of the ring instance. Set this value to 'enabled' to start the ring or 'disabled' to stop it. The value 'running' indicates that the ring is currently configured and running, in which case, the values of node-type and control-vlan cannot be modified.

nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPort.name: nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPort
nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPort.description: The interface index of the primary-port if the 'nmsMEAPSRingNodeType' is 'masterNode', or the ifIndex of the first transit-port if 'transitNode'. Value 0 means that this port is not configured.

nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPortState.name: nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPortState
nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPortState.description: The forwarding state of the primary-port or the first transit-port.

nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPortStatus.name: nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPortStatus
nmsMEAPSRingPrimaryPortStatus.description: The link status of the primary-port or the first transit-port.

nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPort.name: nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPort
nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPort.description: The interface index of the secondary-port if the 'nmsMEAPSRingNodeType' is 'masterNode', or the ifIndex of the second transit-port if 'transitNode'. Value 0 means that this port is not configured.

nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPortState.name: nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPortState
nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPortState.description: The forwarding state of the secondary-port or the second transit-port.

nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPortStatus.name: nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPortStatus
nmsMEAPSRingSecondaryPortStatus.description: The link status of the secondary-port or the second transit-port.
